# AgentTrace desktop — Apple notarization credentials (for `npm run dist`).
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in, OR (preferred) use a keychain profile so no
# secret ever touches your shell/env. .env is gitignored — never commit it.
#
# ── Preferred: keychain profile (secret stays in the macOS login keychain) ──
# Create it once (prompts for the app-specific password, stores it securely):
#   xcrun notarytool store-credentials agenttrace-notary \
#     --apple-id you@example.com --team-id XXXXXXXXXX
# Then reference it by NAME only — no secret in the environment:
APPLE_KEYCHAIN_PROFILE=agenttrace-notary

# ── Fallback: explicit credentials (avoid on shared machines) ──
# Get the app-specific password at appleid.apple.com → Sign-In & Security →
# App-Specific Passwords (shown once). Do NOT `export VAR=<value>` inline in a
# shell — that lands in shell history. Put it in `.env` (gitignored) instead.
# APPLE_ID=you@example.com
# APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD=xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx
# APPLE_TEAM_ID=XXXXXXXXXX
